for blood sugar

00:01:29.150 --> 00:01:34.430 align:middle line:10%
is about 75 to 100
milligrams per deciliter

00:01:34.430 --> 00:01:36.110 align:middle line:10%
on your blood test.

00:01:36.110 --> 00:01:38.810 align:middle line:84%
So if you're over 100,
you're a pre-diabetic.

00:01:38.810 --> 00:01:42.590 align:middle line:84%
If you're over 126,
you're a type 2 diabetic.

00:01:42.590 --> 00:01:44.690 align:middle line:84%
Now, there are
labs out there that

00:01:44.690 --> 00:01:51.200 align:middle line:84%
are still not screening you at
all until you're 118 or 110.

00:01:51.200 --> 00:01:53.852 align:middle line:84%
And studies have shown that
the damage of diabetes--

00:01:53.852 --> 00:01:55.310 align:middle line:84%
and we'll talk
about what that is--

00:01:55.310 --> 00:01:56.895 align:middle line:90%
that doesn't start just at 100.

00:01:56.895 --> 00:01:59.270 align:middle line:84%
There was one study that
showed, if your numbers are just

00:01:59.270 --> 00:02:04.400 align:middle line:84%
over 85, you're at a 40%
increased risk of dying

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:05.810 align:middle line:90%
of a heart attack or stroke.

00:02:05.810 --> 00:02:08.780 align:middle line:84%
So there's a bunch of people
that between 85 and 100.

00:02:08.780 --> 00:02:11.280 align:middle line:84%
Now, 1/3 of the American
population is over 100.

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:12.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Over 100.

00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:14.840 align:middle line:84%
