hospital-approved blood

00:03:02.690 --> 00:03:05.370 align:middle line:84%
sugar monitors so that I can
give them to my patients,

00:03:05.370 --> 00:03:06.920 align:middle line:84%
they could take it home, and
they can check their own blood

00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:07.720 align:middle line:90%
sugar.

00:03:07.720 --> 00:03:09.920 align:middle line:84%
And these are very
healthy people generally,

00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:13.040 align:middle line:84%
and their blood sugars
were 110, 120, 130.

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:16.340 align:middle line:84%
A lot of them full-blown type 2
diabetics and they had no idea.

00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:19.490 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of the symptoms
of diabetes are insidious,

00:03:19.490 --> 00:03:22.477 align:middle line:84%
and what happens
is on the inside.

00:03:22.477 --> 00:03:24.560 align:middle line:84%
The number one thing, when
that blood sugar starts

00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:28.490 align:middle line:84%
to rise after a dessert
or after a Coca-Cola, when

00:03:28.490 --> 00:03:31.230 align:middle line:84%
those numbers start to rise
in your blood a little bit,

00:03:31.230 --> 00:03:33.350 align:middle line:84%
the first thing that happens
is the muscles, which

00:03:33.350 --> 00:03:35.330 align:middle line:84%
are the big gas
guzzlers for your sugar,

00:03:35.330 --> 00:03:37.180 align:middle line:84%
they just go, I can't
take any more sugar.

00:03:37.180 --> 00:03:38.680 align:middle line:84%
I don't even want
to think about it.

00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:40.080 align:middle line:90%
So then it stays in your blood.

00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:42.710 align:middle line:84%
The first thing it does
is converts directly

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:45.710 align:middle line:84%
into fat, belly fat,
hip fat, arm fat.

00:03:45.710 --> 00:03:46.820 align:middle line:90%
That's number one.

00:03:46.820 --> 00:03:50.150 align:middle line:84%
Number two, it converts directly
into LDL cholesterol, which

00:03:50.150 --> 00:03:51.840 align:middle line:90%
is damaging for your arteries.

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:53.630 align:middle line:84%
And number three,
the worst of all,

00:03:53.630 --> 00:03:55.310 align:middle line:90%
is what's called glycation.

00:03:55.310 --> 00:03:59.630 align:middle line:84%
The sugar in your blood attaches
to proteins in your blood

00:03:59.630 --> 00:04:01.070 align:middle line:90%
and clumps your blood.

00:04:01.070 --> 00:04:04.480 align:middle line:84%
It's particularly fond of
two very important proteins,

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:07.670 align:middle line:84%
collagen and elastin,
which makes our skin look

00:04:07.670 --> 00:04:08.960 align:middle line:90%
nice and youthful.

00:04:08.960 --> 00:04:12.080 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't only make us
look old and aged and wrinkled

00:04:12.080 --> 00:04:14.750 align:middle line:84%
on the outside, but it's the
skin on the inside that's

00:04:14.750 --> 00:04:15.680 align:middle line:90%
most important.

00:04:15.680 --> 00:04:17.480 align:middle line:84%
When your arteries
start to wrinkle

00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:20.332 align:middle line:84%
and your intestinal mucosa
and your intestinal tract

00:04:20.332 --> 00:04:22.040 align:middle line:84%
starts to wrinkle,
your respiratory tract

00:04:22.040 --> 00:04:24.800 align:middle line:84%
starts to wrinkle, we've
got some severe problems.

00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:27.900 align:middle line:84%
And what happens, when that
glycation begins to happen,

00:04:27.900 --> 00:04:30.770 align:middle line:84%
it's the number one cause
of cardiovascular disease.

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:32.760 align:middle line:90%
It damages your arteries.

00:04:32.760 --> 00:04:36.540 align:middle line:84%
So the number one killer in
America today is heart disease.

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:38.660 align:middle line:84%
The number one cause
of heart disease

00:04:38.660 --> 00:04:42.033 align:middle line:84%
is this insidious blood
sugar pre-diabetic impact.

00:04:42.033 --> 00:04:43.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: See, now,
that's not something

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:44.783 align:middle line:90%
you hear about that often.

00:04:44.783 --> 00:04:47.480 align:middle line:84%
We only hear about cholesterol
and some other obvious things

00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:49.150 align:middle line:84%
the medical industry
passes on to us.

00:04:49.150 --> 00:04:51.275 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: And this is
the cause of that, really.

00:04:51.275 --> 00:04:52.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:04:52.820 --> 00:04:54.530 align:middle line:84%
I remember years ago
doing an interview

00:04:54.530 --> 00:04:56.960 align:middle line:84%
with Udo Erasmus who wrote
the book "Fats That Heal,

00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:57.890 align:middle line:90%
Fats That Kill."

00:04:57.890 --> 00:04:59.090 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Fantastic book.

00:04:59.090 --> 00:05:00.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Fantastic.

00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:04.220 align:middle line:84%
