me that it was not the fat

00:05:04.220 --> 00:05:06.763 align:middle line:84%
that we eat in our
diet, it was the sugars

00:05:06.763 --> 00:05:08.930 align:middle line:84%
and the simple carbohydrates
we eat in our diet that

00:05:08.930 --> 00:05:10.050 align:middle line:90%
were killing us.

00:05:10.050 --> 00:05:12.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, that was completely
counter to everything

00:05:12.050 --> 00:05:15.200 align:middle line:84%
going on if you look at the
food pyramid, cut out the fats,

00:05:15.200 --> 00:05:16.250 align:middle line:90%
cut out the fats.

00:05:16.250 --> 00:05:18.110 align:middle line:84%
Well, a lot of that
thinking is changing,

00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:21.830 align:middle line:84%
and let's talk about the whole
cycle of simple carbohydrates

00:05:21.830 --> 00:05:25.790 align:middle line:84%
versus, we'll just start
with, versus fats and proteins

00:05:25.790 --> 00:05:28.010 align:middle line:84%
and what it's doing
to our insulin levels.

00:05:28.010 --> 00:05:30.320 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Well, the
