00:26:46.023 --> 00:26:47.940 align:middle line:84%
One of my books is called
"The 3-Season Diet,"

00:26:47.940 --> 00:26:50.220 align:middle line:84%
is understanding that in
the winter, we harvest more

00:26:50.220 --> 00:26:51.390 align:middle line:90%
proteins and fats.

00:26:51.390 --> 00:26:53.190 align:middle line:84%
In the spring,
more leafy greens.

00:26:53.190 --> 00:26:55.110 align:middle line:84%
In the summer, more
high-energy carbohydrates

00:26:55.110 --> 00:26:59.070 align:middle line:84%
to get through the long days
and short nights of summer.

00:26:59.070 --> 00:27:03.150 align:middle line:84%
So the idea is that every
season, the diet shifts.

00:27:03.150 --> 00:27:08.120 align:middle line:84%
So as we begin to start having
meals as opposed to snacks,

00:27:08.120 --> 00:27:10.590 align:middle line:84%
