So you have to realize, again,
eat meals, relax, take time.

00:39:17.040 --> 00:39:19.790 align:middle line:84%
These are the types that
never stop and eat their food.

00:39:19.790 --> 00:39:21.680 align:middle line:84%
They inhale their
food, and they go.

00:39:21.680 --> 00:39:24.980 align:middle line:84%
And in Ayurveda, we always
talk about three things

00:39:24.980 --> 00:39:26.510 align:middle line:90%
that are important for eating--

00:39:26.510 --> 00:39:28.790 align:middle line:90%
how, when, and what you eat.

00:39:28.790 --> 00:39:31.550 align:middle line:84%
And the when we eat
is important-- meals

00:39:31.550 --> 00:39:32.690 align:middle line:90%
versus snacks.

00:39:32.690 --> 00:39:34.010 align:middle line:90%
The what we eat is important.

00:39:34.010 --> 00:39:35.510 align:middle line:84%
And America's all
about what to eat.

00:39:35.510 --> 00:39:37.910 align:middle line:84%
We have diets for every day
of the week for what to eat.

00:39:37.910 --> 00:39:40.237 align:middle line:84%
But reality is it's
more based on eating

00:39:40.237 --> 00:39:42.320 align:middle line:84%
what's in season, which
would be more appropriate.

00:39:42.320 --> 00:39:45.110 align:middle line:84%
But the most important one
of all is how you eat--

00:39:45.110 --> 00:39:47.240 align:middle line:90%
relaxing and taking time.

00:39:47.240 --> 00:39:51.370 align:middle line:84%
And nowadays, unless we have
a book, or a movie, or TV,

00:39:51.370 --> 00:39:54.500 align:middle line:84%
or a phone to read, or a
magazine to flip through,

00:39:54.500 --> 00:39:56.390 align:middle line:84%
we're not comfortable
eating our food.

00:39:56.390 --> 00:39:59.510 align:middle line:84%
So stopping, and relaxing,
and being settled

00:39:59.510 --> 00:40:02.900 align:middle line:84%
allows you to digest
in an efficient manner.

00:40:02.900 --> 00:40:05.630 align:middle line:84%
Probably the biggest piece
of the blood sugar puzzle

00:40:05.630 --> 00:40:06.430 align:middle line:90%
is stress.

00:40:06.430 --> 00:40:07.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:40:07.230 --> 00:40:09.290 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: And we live
in a stressed out world,

00:40:09.290 --> 00:40:11.310 align:middle line:84%
and we're feeding
ourselves with comfort,

00:40:11.310 --> 00:40:13.550 align:middle line:90%
stress-relieving foods.

00:40:13.550 --> 00:40:17.605 align:middle line:84%
And if we could just all go to
the beach, or go on vacation,

00:40:17.605 --> 00:40:21.040 align:middle line:84%
and just chill, the blood
sugar changes dramatically.

00:40:21.040 --> 00:40:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And then you have your
Kapha body type, which

00:40:22.970 --> 00:40:24.800 align:middle line:90%
is like the spring body type.

00:40:24.800 --> 00:40:27.860 align:middle line:84%
The Pitta types are the
fiery, summer types.

00:40:27.860 --> 00:40:29.450 align:middle line:84%
Then you have your
spring body types--

00:40:29.450 --> 00:40:32.680 align:middle line:84%
Earth and water, heavy,
easygoing, mellow.

00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:34.420 align:middle line:90%
They're hypometabolic.

00:40:34.420 --> 00:40:36.710 align:middle line:84%
So they don't have
a fast metabolism.

00:40:36.710 --> 00:40:39.250 align:middle line:84%
And in our culture,
with six meals a day,

00:40:39.250 --> 00:40:41.290 align:middle line:84%
lots of high
glycemic foods, they

00:40:41.290 --> 00:40:42.850 align:middle line:90%
don't have a fighting chance.

00:40:42.850 --> 00:40:46.240 align:middle line:84%
That hypometabolic body type,
that slow metabolic system,

00:40:46.240 --> 00:40:49.210 align:middle line:84%
is going to store fat, and gain
weight, and predispose them

00:40:49.210 --> 00:40:52.038 align:middle line:84%
to prediabetes and diabetes
for sure, as well as weight.

00:40:52.038 --> 00:40:53.455 align:middle line:84%
So they have to
move and exercise.

00:40:53.455 --> 00:40:55.855 align:middle line:84%
And we should probably talk
about the value of exercise

00:40:55.855 --> 00:40:56.710 align:middle line:90%
with blood sugar--

00:40:56.710 --> 00:40:56.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, we will.

00:40:56.980 --> 00:40:58.980 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: --because
that's important as well.

00:40:58.980 --> 00:41:03.052 align:middle line:84%
But these body types definitely
all can succumb to diabetes,

00:41:03.052 --> 00:41:04.510 align:middle line:84%
and that's why we
have an epidemic.

00:41:04.510 --> 00:41:05.920 align:middle line:90%
It's everybody.

00:41:05.920 --> 00:41:11.080 align:middle line:84%
But we get there based on our
own individual predispositions.

00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:13.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And each of those
body types, from the thimbleful

00:41:13.780 --> 00:41:14.630 align:middle line:90%
of understanding.

