00:46:30.710 --> 00:46:32.780 align:middle line:84%
We're not even eating
close to what they eat.

00:46:32.780 --> 00:46:36.470 align:middle line:84%
But those vegetables
require us to chew.

00:46:36.470 --> 00:46:40.130 align:middle line:84%
And it creates a whole shift
in our brain chemistry.

00:46:40.130 --> 00:46:44.070 align:middle line:84%
It prepares the
digestive system.

00:46:44.070 --> 00:46:46.880 align:middle line:84%
It provides the fiber to
escort the toxins out.

00:46:46.880 --> 00:46:47.840 align:middle line:90%
It's so critical.

00:46:47.840 --> 00:46:50.930 align:middle line:84%
I don't mind adding a
little juice or protein

00:46:50.930 --> 00:46:53.360 align:middle line:84%
powders to the mix, but
that should not be a meal.

00:46:53.360 --> 00:46:55.632 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we should
not rely on greens.

00:46:55.632 --> 00:46:57.590 align:middle line:84%
As you said earlier,
salad's not a meal either.

00:46:57.590 --> 00:46:59.360 align:middle line:84%
Again, it goes back
to this balance.

00:46:59.360 --> 00:46:59.680 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Right.

00:46:59.680 --> 00:47:01.388 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now
let's talk about Pitta.

00:47:01.388 --> 00:47:04.580 align:middle line:84%
What does an ideal spectrum
of food look like for Pitta

00:47:04.580 --> 00:47:06.670 align:middle line:84%
compared to what we would
normally do as Pittas?

00:47:06.670 --> 00:47:08.420 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Well, the
Vatas will probably

00:47:08.420 --> 00:47:11.157 align:middle line:84%
need smaller meals because
they have a smaller digestion.

00:47:11.157 --> 00:47:12.740 align:middle line:84%
And they still need
three meals a day.

00:47:12.740 --> 00:47:13.910 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, I'll
actually let them

00:47:13.910 --> 00:47:15.500 align:middle line:84%
have four meals to get
started, and then they

00:47:15.500 --> 00:47:17.212 align:middle line:84%
can work their blood
sugar to have three.

00:47:17.212 --> 00:47:18.920 align:middle line:84%
And remember, the big
piece of the puzzle

00:47:18.920 --> 00:47:20.837 align:middle line:84%
here is when you're going
from six meals a day

00:47:20.837 --> 00:47:24.170 align:middle line:84%
to three meals a day, it
has to be without strain.

00:47:24.170 --> 00:47:25.880 align:middle line:84%
Soon as you're
craving something,

00:47:25.880 --> 00:47:27.680 align:middle line:90%
your blood sugar is crashing.

00:47:27.680 --> 00:47:29.960 align:middle line:84%
So eat a snack, make
it a healthy snack.

00:47:29.960 --> 00:47:32.490 align:middle line:84%
But then tomorrow,
have a bigger lunch,

00:47:32.490 --> 00:47:34.490 align:middle line:84%
and see if you can make
the energy last a little

00:47:34.490 --> 00:47:35.050 align:middle line:90%
bit longer.

00:47:35.050 --> 00:47:36.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, keep looking
to perfect that balance.

00:47:36.160 --> 00:47:37.035 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Work it.

00:47:37.035 --> 00:47:39.200 align:middle line:84%
Pitta types, they
have a big furnace,

00:47:39.200 --> 00:47:40.740 align:middle line:90%
and they need a lot of fuel.

00:47:40.740 --> 00:47:42.807 align:middle line:84%
So they're going to
need higher quantities.

00:47:42.807 --> 00:47:44.390 align:middle line:84%
You want to make
sure that they're not

00:47:44.390 --> 00:47:46.340 align:middle line:84%
eating a lot of spicy
food because that can

00:47:46.340 --> 00:47:47.880 align:middle line:90%
overheat them and inflame them.

00:47:47.880 --> 00:47:50.758 align:middle line:84%
And diabetes, or prediabetes,
is actually inflammation

00:47:50.758 --> 00:47:52.550 align:middle line:84%
of either the gut, the
liver, the pancreas,

00:47:52.550 --> 00:47:54.770 align:middle line:84%
one of those three, or
all three get inflamed.

00:47:54.770 --> 00:47:58.400 align:middle line:84%
And Pitta types, they
tend towards inflammation.

00:47:58.400 --> 00:48:01.220 align:middle line:84%
And so they have to make
sure they're eating good.

00:48:01.220 --> 00:48:03.080 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the
cooling foods are

00:48:03.080 --> 00:48:05.060 align:middle line:84%
going to be the greens
and the bitters.

00:48:05.060 --> 00:48:06.728 align:middle line:90%
The pungent foods, or--

00:48:06.728 --> 00:48:09.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry-- the bitter foods,
and the astringent foods,

00:48:09.020 --> 00:48:11.870 align:middle line:84%
the greens, and the
vegetables, and the beans,

00:48:11.870 --> 00:48:13.760 align:middle line:90%
are very cooling for the body.

00:48:13.760 --> 00:48:18.530 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the Pitta types
who need big doses of sugar

00:48:18.530 --> 00:48:22.250 align:middle line:84%
into the brain right away,
they crave potatoes, and meats,

00:48:22.250 --> 00:48:26.870 align:middle line:84%
and burgers, and fries, and
that quick, high-carb injection

00:48:26.870 --> 00:48:29.120 align:middle line:84%
to the brain, which,
of course, gives them

00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:30.510 align:middle line:90%
the energy they need.

00:48:30.510 --> 00:48:33.260 align:middle line:84%
But it actually brews the
underlying inflammation

00:48:33.260 --> 00:48:34.505 align:middle line:90%
which we don't want to have.

00:48:34.505 --> 00:48:35.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, Kapha.

00:48:35.690 --> 00:48:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Kapha types
are easygoing, mellow, slow

00:48:38.060 --> 00:48:39.410 align:middle line:90%
metabolic body types.

00:48:39.410 --> 00:48:43.280 align:middle line:84%
They really require
three tastes--

00:48:43.280 --> 00:48:46.490 align:middle line:90%
pungent, bitter, and astringent.

00:48:46.490 --> 00:48:48.530 align:middle line:84%
So they live in
a world, America,

00:48:48.530 --> 00:48:50.600 align:middle line:84%
that is a sweet,
sour, and salty world,

00:48:50.600 --> 00:48:53.090 align:middle line:84%
and they require pungent,
bitter, and astringent.

00:48:53.090 --> 00:48:54.860 align:middle line:84%
So they require
spicy food to burn up

00:48:54.860 --> 00:48:58.940 align:middle line:84%
the fat, astringent foods to
clean and detoxify, and bitter

00:48:58.940 --> 00:49:00.530 align:middle line:84%
foods to flush the
system with more

00:49:00.530 --> 00:49:02.478 align:middle line:84%
alkaline, lymphatic,
moving agents.

00:49:02.478 --> 00:49:04.770 align:middle line:84%
And we live in a world where
it's exactly the opposite.

00:49:04.770 --> 00:49:04.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:49:04.910 --> 00:49:06.535 align:middle line:84%
Most of the people
I know who are Kapha

00:49:06.535 --> 00:49:09.070 align:middle line:90%
constitutions like ice cream--

00:49:09.070 --> 00:49:09.870 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Pizza.

00:49:09.870 --> 00:49:10.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:49:10.670 --> 00:49:11.880 align:middle line:90%
Popcorn and pizza.

00:49:11.880 --> 00:49:11.950 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:49:11.950 --> 00:49:12.770 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Yeah.

00:49:12.770 --> 00:49:14.300 align:middle line:84%
So these are issues
we have to be careful.

00:49:14.300 --> 00:49:16.467 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, so basically,
they're eating exactly

00:49:16.467 --> 00:49:17.400 align:middle line:90%
out of their type.

00:49:17.400 --> 00:49:17.830 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Yeah.

00:49:17.830 --> 00:49:18.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:49:18.630 --> 00:49:20.210 align:middle line:90%
And so what about breakfast?

00:49:20.210 --> 00:49:22.640 align:middle line:84%
Not everybody's thinking
in terms of rice,

00:49:22.640 --> 00:49:24.960 align:middle line:84%
and protein, and
greens for breakfast.

00:49:24.960 --> 00:49:25.760 align:middle line:90%
What do you have?

00:49:25.760 --> 00:49:27.290 align:middle line:84%
What would you
recommend for breakfast?

00:49:27.290 --> 00:49:28.910 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Well,
breakfast can vary.

00:49:28.910 --> 00:49:30.558 align:middle line:90%
It can be eggs, which are good.

00:49:30.558 --> 00:49:32.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Is that
good for all types?

00:49:32.100 --> 00:49:32.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: It can
be good for all types.

00:49:32.930 --> 00:49:33.732 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:49:33.732 --> 00:49:35.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: I think that
based on the seasons,

00:49:35.690 --> 00:49:37.070 align:middle line:84%
you can make some adjustment,
but eggs are good.

00:49:37.070 --> 00:49:38.880 align:middle line:84%
A good piece of good,
sprouted-grain bread

00:49:38.880 --> 00:49:39.680 align:middle line:90%
can be good.

00:49:39.680 --> 00:49:41.430 align:middle line:84%
Ezekiel bread, something
like that's good.

00:49:41.430 --> 00:49:42.320 align:middle line:90%
That's for starch.

00:49:42.320 --> 00:49:43.700 align:middle line:84%
And now you need
your vegetables.

00:49:43.700 --> 00:49:49.160 align:middle line:84%
Well, now you can get
the kale, or the greens,

00:49:49.160 --> 00:49:51.020 align:middle line:84%
or the leafy baby greens
already pre-washed.

00:49:51.020 --> 00:49:52.040 align:middle line:84%
Just pull it out,
and you can have

00:49:52.040 --> 00:49:54.320 align:middle line:84%
that with a cup of herbal
tea with your breakfast,

00:49:54.320 --> 00:49:55.130 align:middle line:90%
and it's great.

00:49:55.130 --> 00:49:56.000 align:middle line:90%
You've got your greens.

00:49:56.000 --> 00:49:57.020 align:middle line:84%
And believe it or
not, you acquire

00:49:57.020 --> 00:49:58.062 align:middle line:90%
a taste for these things.

00:49:58.062 --> 00:50:00.050 align:middle line:84%
Because inside that
green stuff is sugar.

00:50:00.050 --> 00:50:01.110 align:middle line:90%
That's what's in there.

00:50:01.110 --> 00:50:03.470 align:middle line:84%
So when you chew it, you
actually acquire a taste.

00:50:03.470 --> 00:50:05.840 align:middle line:84%
You change your brain
chemistry to actually

00:50:05.840 --> 00:50:08.360 align:middle line:84%
be satisfied with something
green versus something

00:50:08.360 --> 00:50:10.502 align:middle line:84%
super sweet, like the
sugar in your coffee.

00:50:10.502 --> 00:50:11.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we
just have to change

00:50:11.960 --> 00:50:13.100 align:middle line:90%
this paradigm of thinking.

00:50:13.100 --> 00:50:14.500 align:middle line:84%
Vegetables are cool
in the morning.

00:50:14.500 --> 00:50:14.630 align:middle line:90%
It's fine.

00:50:14.630 --> 00:50:15.050 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: They are.

00:50:15.050 --> 00:50:15.420 align:middle line:90%
They can be.

00:50:15.420 --> 00:50:15.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The whole
thing, the leaves--

00:50:15.910 --> 00:50:16.920 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Absolutely.

00:50:16.920 --> 00:50:18.087 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Especially leaves.

00:50:18.087 --> 00:50:20.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Or like
celery and a nut butter.

00:50:20.120 --> 00:50:20.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:50:20.300 --> 00:50:21.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: That's
green, and that's

00:50:21.030 --> 00:50:21.440 align:middle line:90%
another way of doing breakfast.

00:50:21.440 --> 00:50:22.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I love
that in the morning.

00:50:22.190 --> 00:50:22.830 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: That's great.

00:50:22.830 --> 00:50:22.920 align:middle line:90%
Yep.

00:50:22.920 --> 00:50:24.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Almond butter
and celery, love it.

00:50:24.100 --> 00:50:25.183 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Yep, perfect.

00:50:25.183 --> 00:50:27.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now
what about exercise?

00:50:27.110 --> 00:50:29.210 align:middle line:90%
And let's do this for--

00:50:29.210 --> 00:50:31.003 align:middle line:84%
however you choose
to break it-- well,

00:50:31.003 --> 00:50:32.420 align:middle line:84%
we only have about
5 minutes left,

00:50:32.420 --> 00:50:34.910 align:middle line:84%
so we want to talk about
exercise and then blood

00:50:34.910 --> 00:50:35.750 align:middle line:90%
monitoring.

00:50:35.750 --> 00:50:38.660 align:middle line:84%
So encapsulate exercise
for us, because I

00:50:38.660 --> 00:50:40.070 align:middle line:84%
know different
constitutions need

00:50:40.070 --> 00:50:41.450 align:middle line:90%
a different kind of exercise.

00:50:41.450 --> 00:50:43.533 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Everybody
needs a different exercise.

00:50:43.533 --> 00:50:45.380 align:middle line:90%
Vata types are hypermetabolic.

00:50:45.380 --> 00:50:47.810 align:middle line:84%
So that means fast moving,
thinking all the time,

00:50:47.810 --> 00:50:50.270 align:middle line:84%
90 miles an hour in their
brain, they need to slow down.

00:50:50.270 --> 00:50:50.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yoga?

00:50:50.660 --> 00:50:51.230 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: So yoga.

00:50:51.230 --> 00:50:51.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:50:51.560 --> 00:50:53.060 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: And hiking
is great for them.

00:50:53.060 --> 00:50:55.352 align:middle line:84%
Pitta types are fiery, and
aggressive, and competitive,

00:50:55.352 --> 00:50:58.380 align:middle line:84%
and driven, and they tend to
be very, very competitive,

00:50:58.380 --> 00:51:00.620 align:middle line:84%
so they need exercises
that are relaxing.

00:51:00.620 --> 00:51:03.423 align:middle line:84%
Yoga is good, but they also
need aerobic activity as well.

00:51:03.423 --> 00:51:05.840 align:middle line:84%
But something that's beautiful,
like skiing, where they're

00:51:05.840 --> 00:51:07.295 align:middle line:90%
actually in beautiful places.

00:51:07.295 --> 00:51:07.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Dancing.

00:51:07.550 --> 00:51:07.820 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Dancing.

00:51:07.820 --> 00:51:08.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Things that
you like doing anyway.

00:51:08.740 --> 00:51:09.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: That
you love doing.

00:51:09.380 --> 00:51:10.400 align:middle line:90%
Things that they love to do.

00:51:10.400 --> 00:51:11.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What about hiking?

00:51:11.120 --> 00:51:11.950 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Not
for winning, yes.

00:51:11.950 --> 00:51:12.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:51:12.080 --> 00:51:13.370 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Not just to win.

00:51:13.370 --> 00:51:14.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Not just running.

00:51:14.290 --> 00:51:15.860 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Not another
competitive venture, right?

00:51:15.860 --> 00:51:16.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:51:16.660 --> 00:51:19.410 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: And then Kapha
types, just give anything.

00:51:19.410 --> 00:51:20.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Move.

00:51:20.210 --> 00:51:21.350 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Anything, yes.

00:51:21.350 --> 00:51:23.870 align:middle line:84%
Anything will take--
bike riding, running,

00:51:23.870 --> 00:51:26.590 align:middle line:84%
but they need to move
their body for sure.

00:51:26.590 --> 00:51:31.850 align:middle line:84%
Now blood sugar,
when the sugar goes

00:51:31.850 --> 00:51:34.610 align:middle line:84%
high in your blood,
the first system that

00:51:34.610 --> 00:51:38.730 align:middle line:84%
shut down the ability to suck it
up, the sugar, is your muscles.

00:51:38.730 --> 00:51:42.000 align:middle line:84%
So the muscles, they cause
the insulin resistance.

00:51:42.000 --> 00:51:45.620 align:middle line:84%
So we can use exercise to
actually reinstate sugar back

00:51:45.620 --> 00:51:47.630 align:middle line:84%
into those muscles,
and use your muscles

00:51:47.630 --> 00:51:49.370 align:middle line:84%
to be the big gas
guzzlers for that sugar

00:51:49.370 --> 00:51:51.370 align:middle line:84%
and take the stress off
the rest of your system.

00:51:51.370 --> 00:51:52.940 align:middle line:90%
It's a huge opportunity.

00:51:52.940 --> 00:51:54.100 align:middle line:90%
Most people don't do it.

00:51:54.100 --> 00:51:55.850 align:middle line:84%
Now if I asked you,
when was the last time

00:51:55.850 --> 00:51:58.160 align:middle line:90%
you ran as fast as you could?

00:51:58.160 --> 00:51:59.588 align:middle line:90%
What would you say?

00:51:59.588 --> 00:52:01.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A couple
days ago, but that

00:52:01.130 --> 00:52:04.260 align:middle line:84%
was only because I had
to run because I was late

00:52:04.260 --> 00:52:05.060 align:middle line:90%
for something.

00:52:05.060 --> 00:52:05.950 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: OK, good.

00:52:05.950 --> 00:52:07.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But normally,
I don't run full speed.

00:52:07.560 --> 00:52:08.720 align:middle line:84%
I might jog a little,
but mostly walk.

00:52:08.720 --> 00:52:09.680 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: Now if
you ask a 12-year-old,

00:52:09.680 --> 00:52:10.750 align:middle line:84%
hey, when was the
last time you ran?

00:52:10.750 --> 00:52:11.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Every day.

00:52:11.430 --> 00:52:12.460 align:middle line:90%
I used to run every day.

00:52:12.460 --> 00:52:12.880 align:middle line:90%
I loved running.

00:52:12.880 --> 00:52:13.070 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Right.

00:52:13.070 --> 00:52:13.330 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:52:13.330 --> 00:52:14.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:52:14.130 --> 00:52:16.680 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: So kids use their
fast-twitch muscle fibers

00:52:16.680 --> 00:52:17.480 align:middle line:90%
every day.

00:52:17.480 --> 00:52:20.082 align:middle line:84%
As we become adults, we
do yoga, we go hiking,

00:52:20.082 --> 00:52:22.290 align:middle line:84%
and we don't use our body
using the fast-twitch part.

00:52:22.290 --> 00:52:24.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But we're afraid
we're going to strain something,

00:52:24.380 --> 00:52:26.310 align:middle line:84%
hurt ourselves, pull
a muscle, hamstring--

00:52:26.310 --> 00:52:27.360 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: But there's
ways you can do it.

00:52:27.360 --> 00:52:29.027 align:middle line:84%
You can take two tuna
fish cans, and you

00:52:29.027 --> 00:52:30.320 align:middle line:90%
can go like this really fast.

00:52:30.320 --> 00:52:30.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:52:30.680 --> 00:52:31.260 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: You can punch.

00:52:31.260 --> 00:52:33.740 align:middle line:84%
You can just step up and down
your stairs in your house

00:52:33.740 --> 00:52:34.760 align:middle line:90%
as fast as you could.

00:52:34.760 --> 00:52:36.710 align:middle line:84%
And when you use
fast-twitch fibers,

00:52:36.710 --> 00:52:38.837 align:middle line:84%
it takes all the sugar
out of your blood.

00:52:38.837 --> 00:52:39.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, interesting.

00:52:39.920 --> 00:52:40.740 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD:
Slow-twitch fibers--

00:52:40.740 --> 00:52:41.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Intervals.

00:52:41.210 --> 00:52:43.490 align:middle line:84%
That's where Mercola and
this whole interval thing

00:52:43.490 --> 00:52:44.480 align:middle line:90%
is really handy.

00:52:44.480 --> 00:52:45.280 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Right.

00:52:45.280 --> 00:52:47.690 align:middle line:84%
So fast-twitch activation
pulls the sugar.

00:52:47.690 --> 00:52:51.380 align:middle line:84%
Slow, long duration
activities burn fat fast,

00:52:51.380 --> 00:52:52.220 align:middle line:90%
which burns sugar.

00:52:52.220 --> 00:52:54.560 align:middle line:84%
